The word puzzle in the image is a "rebus" puzzle.

Here's how it is solved:
- The image shows an "S" and a horseshoe (which is also called a “U”);
- When placed together, this forms the word "Shoe";
- Below it, there is an image of a hand;
- The word "Shoe" plus the image of the hand gives us "Shoe-hand".

When we combine and pronounce these together, it sounds like "shoehand", which corresponds to "shoehorn".

Therefore, the answer to the rebus puzzle is "Shoehorn".
